{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1390742878,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNjMxMzc2OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/43","origin":"github"},"title":"(core) type-pooled memory management","message":"As a prelude to moving image decoding / processing etc. outside the main process, the current malloc() free() use should be overhauled to use typed pools with proper madvise/mprotect settings, and on platforms that support it, ensure that sensitive or superflous (textures!) don't get added to core- dumps.\n\nDue to the extremely planar execution path (e.g. events -\u003e render -\u003e ...) the mprotect usage patterns should reflect this, so that the relevant pools alternate between R ^ W (and never X).","files":null}]}